{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:sirach.20",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 20 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:1",
      "text": "There is a reproof that is not comely: again, some man holdeth his tongue, and he is wise.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:2",
      "text": "It is much better to reprove, than to be angry secretly: and he that confesseth his fault shall be preserved from hurt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:3",
      "text": "How good is it, when thou art reproved, to shew repentance! for so shalt thou escape wilful sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:4",
      "text": "As is the lust of an eunuch to deflower a virgin; so is he that executeth judgement with violence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:5",
      "text": "There is one that keepeth silence, and is found wise: and another by much babbling becometh hateful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:6",
      "text": "Some man holdeth his tongue, because he hath not to answer: and some keepeth silence, knowing his time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:7",
      "text": "A wise man will hold his tongue till he see opportunity: but a babbler and a fool will regard no time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:8",
      "text": "He that useth many words shall be abhorred; and he that taketh to himself authority therein shall be hated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:9",
      "text": "There is a sinner that hath good success in evil things; and there is a gain that turneth to loss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:10",
      "text": "There is a gift that shall not profit thee; and there is a gift whose recompence is double.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:11",
      "text": "There is an abasement because of glory; and there is that lifteth up his head from a low estate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:12",
      "text": "There is that buyeth much for a little, and repayeth it sevenfold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:13",
      "text": "A wise man by his words maketh him beloved: but the graces of fools shall be poured out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:14",
      "text": "The gift of a fool shall do thee no good when thou hast it; neither yet of the envious for his necessity: for he looketh to receive many things for one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:15",
      "text": "He giveth little, and upbraideth much; he openeth his mouth like a crier; to day he lendeth, and to morrow will he ask it again: such an one is to be hated of God and man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:16",
      "text": "The fool saith, I have no friends, I have no thank for all my good deeds, and they that eat my bread speak evil of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:17",
      "text": "How oft, and of how many shall he be laughed to scorn! for he knoweth not aright what it is to have; and it is all one unto him as if he had it not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:18",
      "text": "To slip upon a pavement is better than to slip with the tongue: so the fall of the wicked shall come speedily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:19",
      "text": "An unseasonable tale will always be in the mouth of the unwise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:20",
      "text": "A wise sentence shall be rejected when it cometh out of a fool’s mouth; for he will not speak it in due season.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:21",
      "text": "There is that is hindered from sinning through want: and when he taketh rest, he shall not be troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:22",
      "text": "There is that destroyeth his own soul through bashfulness, and by accepting of persons overthroweth himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:23",
      "text": "There is that for bashfulness promiseth to his friend, and maketh him his enemy for nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:24",
      "text": "A lie is a foul blot in a man, yet it is continually in the mouth of the untaught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:25",
      "text": "A thief is better than a man that is accustomed to lie: but they both shall have destruction to heritage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:26",
      "text": "The disposition of a liar is dishonourable, and his shame is ever with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:27",
      "text": "A wise man shall promote himself to honour with his words: and he that hath understanding will please great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:28",
      "text": "He that tilleth his land shall increase his heap: and he that pleaseth great men shall get pardon for iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:29",
      "text": "Presents and gifts blind the eyes of the wise, and stop up his mouth that he cannot reprove.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:30",
      "text": "Wisdom that is hid, and treasure that is hoarded up, what profit is in them both?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:31",
      "text": "Better is he that hideth his folly than a man that hideth his wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.20.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 20:32",
      "text": "Necessary patience in seeking the Lord is better than he that leadeth his life without a guide.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
